HEADWORD: Particle physics
<hw>Par"ti*cle phys`ics</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>That
branch of physics which investigates the nature of matter, and in
particular the properties and behavior of the elementary particles
(fundamental particles), of which matter is composed. Included in this
field is the more specialized branch of <er>high-energy
physics</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

